<collectingCountry box="[454,553,261,287]" name="Portugal" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: three northern provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,224,467]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,297,323]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Ecology.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[338,433,297,323]" name="Portugal" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Portugal</collectingCountry>
this species was collected in diverse biotopes, with nearly half of them situated in parks. In northwestern Europe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" box="[429,556,334,359]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Dolichopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signatus">
<emphasis box="[429,556,334,359]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">D. signatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly found in humid heathland and humid deciduous woodland (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M. &amp; Grootaert, P." pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="173 - 186" refId="ref34910" refString="Pollet, M. &amp; Grootaert, P. (1987) Ecological data on Dolichopodidae (Diptera) from a woodland ecosystem. I. Colour preference, detailed distribution and comparison between different sampling techniques. Bulletin de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 57, 173 - 186." type="journal article" year="1987">Pollet &amp; Grootaert 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Maes, D. &amp; Pollet, M." box="[336,565,369,395]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="419 - 438" refId="ref32796" refString="Maes, D. &amp; Pollet, M. (1997) Dolichopodid communities (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) in ' De Kempen' (eastern Belgium): biodiversity, faunistics and ecology. Bulletin et Annales de la Societe royale belge d'Entomologie, 133, 419 - 438." type="journal article" year="1997">Maes &amp; Pollet 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,224,467]" box="[199,700,404,431]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,404,431]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
